channel.title: New computers
channel.description:

[code] Color Black Operating System Operating System Microsoft Windows 7 Home Premium (64-bit) Case & Motherboard Form Factor Tower North Bridge Chipset Intel H57 Express Processor CPU Brand Intel # of Cores 2 CPU Type Core i5 CPU Speed 650 (3.2GHz) Turbo Boost Speed Up to 3.46GHz Level 3 Cache 4MB Smart Cache 4MB FSB 2.5 GT/s CPU Socket LGA 1156 CPUs Installed 1 CPUs Supported 1 Memory Total Memory 8GB Memory Speed DDR3-1333 Form Factor 240-pin DIMM Memory Configuration 4 x 2GB Memory Slots (Total) 4 Memory Slots (Available) 0 Hard Drive HD Capacity 1TB HD Interface SATA HD RPM Variable Multimedia Drives Optical Drives Included 1 Optical Drive SuperMulti DVD±RW Optical Drive Specs SuperMulti DVD±RW - Write Max: 16X DVD±R, 6X DVD-RW, 8X DVD+RW, 8X DVD±R DL, 5X DVD-RAM, 48X CD-R, 32X CD-RW; Read Max: 16X DVD-ROM, 40X CD-ROM Video Video Memory 1GB dedicated GPU Interface PCIe x16 Audio Audio System High Definition Audio Audio Channels 5.1 Communications LAN Gigabit LAN LAN Data Rate Speed 10/100/1000Mbps WLAN Wireless LAN Card Reader Card Reader Multi-in-One Digital Media Card Reader Front Panel Ports USB 2.0 4 Back Panel Ports PS/2 2 VGA 15-pin 1 DVI 1 HDMI 1 LAN RJ-45 1 Audio 3 Expansion Bays External 5.25" Bays (Total) 2 External 5.25" Bays (Available) 1 Internal 3.5" Bays (Total) 3 Internal 3.5" Bays (Available) 2 Expansion Slots PCIe x16 Slots (Total) 1 PCIe x16 Slots (Available) 0 PCIe x1 Slots (Total) 2 PCIe x1 Slots (Available) 1 PCI Slots (Total) 1 PCI Slots (Available) 1 Keyboard Keyboard Multimedia Mouse Mouse Optical Power Power Supply 300 Watt [/code]

item.title: New computers
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

I’ll make a suggestion:

$119: CPU - AMD Phenom Quad Core Black Edition (as much as I dislike AMD, their cpus are so much cheaper).
$189: Motherboard - Asus Sabertooth 990x
$29: 4GB RAM - Kingston Hyperx @ 1600mhz 4gb is all you need really.
$175: Graphics - EVGA Superclocked GTX460

Then just find a cheap HDD ($40), optical drive ($20), and a case (with psu $100, without around $40+ cost of psu, providing these are pretty cheap boxy cases).

Pretty much all you need, not sure what that adds to, I’m from UK so them last few prices may not be accurate, but this would be quite a mean little budget gaming machine.

edit: yeah that comes out way under $700 which is not at all bad, this’ll max most games.
